default9.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe effectiveness of measures to reduce the use of single-use carrier bags can be 
defaultincreased with exemptions for compostable bags.
default&#xa0;
default9.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUnlike single-use bags these compostable bags have significantly lower environmental impact – and can completely biodegrade quickly in most natural environments. They have no further impact on wildlife or the food chain.
default&#xa0;
default9.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe compostable bio-plastics industry is a research driven sector, and an alternative to the traditional European petrochemical industry which is struggling to compete with high fuel costs outside Europe.
default&#xa0;
default9.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCompostable bags can play a significant role in the reducing the volume of food waste going to landfill – and improve the quality of 
defaultcompostable materials passed onto the agricultural sector. By providing them through supermarkets it can reduce the costs to councils of providing compostable bin liners.
